obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `THE TOKYO CONVENTION ACT, 1975`
  line `A CT N O. 20 OF 1975`
  line `[8 th May, 1975. ]`
  line `An Act to give effect to the Convention on offences and certain other acts committed on board`
  line aircraft.
  line `W HEREAS a Convention on offences and certain other acts committed on board aircraft was on the`
  line `Fourteenth day of September, 1963, signed at Tokyo;`
  line `A ND W HEREAS it is expedient that India should accede to the said Convention and should make`
  line `provisions for gi ving effect theret o;`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Twenty - sixth Year of the R epublic of India as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMIN A RY`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Tokyo Convention`
  line `Act, 1975.`
  line `( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line `( 3 ) It shall come into force on such date 1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `D EFINITIONS`
  line `2. Definitions. — ( 1 ) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “ aircraft ” means any aircraft, whether or not reg istered in India, other than —`
  line `( i ) a military aircraft; or`
  line `( ii ) an aircraft belonging to, or exclusively employed in the service of, the State;`
  line `( b ) “ appropriate authority ” means —`
  line `( i ) in relation to India, any police office r not below the rank of an Assistant Sub - Inspector o r`
  line `any Immigration Officer, and`
  line `( ii ) in relation to any other country, being a Convention country, any officer having functions`
  line `corresponding to the functions in India either of a police officer not below the rank of an`
  line `Assistant Sub - Inspector or of an Immigration Officer;`
  line `( c ) “ commander ”, in relation t o an aircraft, means the member of the crew designated as`
  line `commander of the aircraft by the operator thereof, or failing such a person, the person who is for the`
  line `time being the pilot in command of the aircraft;`
  line `( d ) “ Convention country ” means a country in which the Tokyo Convention is for the time being`
  line `in force;`
  line `( e ) “ Indian registered aircraft ” means an aircraft —`
  line `( A ) which is for the time being registered in India;`
  line `1. 1st January, 1976, vide notification No. S.O. 5426, dated 17th December, 1975, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3( ii ).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-3
  sectionNo (3)
